    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Flutes with two finger holes and one thumbhole. Usually played in tandem with a drum. A full diatonic scale could be achieved by over-blowing and many folk tunes and dances were thus playable.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
